snippet.textDisplay: i make this all the time.... u got a bum recipe dude... here's how this is done...  coat the balls in corn flakes, freeze solid, then  you dip them in tempura batter (which cant be veganized...since no egg replacers work the same in tempura batter, ive tried.) so just use flour and ice cold water for the batter.  and there are 2 variations.. u can fry it then re-batter and re-fry to get a thicker coating on it. also,  ,you can  use slices of  cake on top of the corn flakes, then dip it in the batter for a yet even thicker coating. i love doing this on new years eve, always a HUGE HIT!!

Maybe someone has said this but I haven't see it yes so Dear Julien,
Don't shape ice cream with your hands boi use cling film/saran wrap.
